Schema, RLS, and triggers are defined in `docs/DATA_MODEL.md`; do not change schema without updating it.

Rules:
- Use relational Supabase tables; do not create one giant product JSON object.
- RLS defaults: products, images, offers, Eazy Scores, and rating summaries are publicly readable; users can only insert/update/delete their own `user_ratings` rows.
- Trusted Community Score recalculation happens in a database trigger/function or server-side logic, never only on the client.
- Never expose service-role keys in client code.

Schema, RLS, migration, and contract work follows the routine in `skills/supabase-schema-change/SKILL.md`.
